-- BAE Closes Pension Plan for New Employees, Sunday Times Says
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2012-04-01T09:00:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-01/bae-closes-pension-plan-for-new-employees-sunday-times-says.html
BAE Systems Plc (BA/)  has shut its final
salary  pension plan  to new workers to help control its pension
deficit, the  Sunday Times reported , without saying how it
obtained the information.  The company is replacing the arrangement with a defined
contribution savings plan, the newspaper said. The pension
deficit climbed to 4.2 billion pounds ($6.7 billion) last year
from 3.1 billion pounds in 2010, the newspaper reported.  The defense company will also seek approval for a new
executive share-option plan at its annual meeting, the Sunday
Times said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
